      • find

        public AbstractConfigNode find(AbstractConfigNode node,
                               java.lang.String path)
        Find the configuration node at the specified path under the specified node.

        Path is specified as a (dot) notation with the following additions. Example: node1.node2.@attr1 - "@" denotes an attribute to search for under the specified path node1.node2.#param1 - "#" denotes a parameter to search for under the specified path

        Parameters:
        node - - Configuration node to search under.
        path - - Path to search for.
        Returns:
        - Configuration Node or NULL.

      • find

        public AbstractConfigNode find(java.lang.String path)
        Find the configuration node at the specified path under the root node.

        Path is specified as a (dot) notation with the following additions. Example: node1.node2.@attr1 - "@" denotes an attribute to search for under the specified path node1.node2.#param1 - "#" denotes a parameter to search for under the specified path

        Parameters:
        path - - Path to search for.
        Returns:
        - Configuration Node or NULL.

      • resolvedProperties

        public ConfigPropertiesNode resolvedProperties(AbstractConfigNode node)
        Get all the defined properties till this node. Properties are defined in scope an can be overridden by subsequent nodes. This method will return a set of properties defined till the root node in this nodes ancestor path.
        Parameters:
        node - - Node to get properties for.
        Returns:
        - Aggregated properties set.
